            <h3>City of San Fernando’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Visit the San Fernando Heritage District and take a kalesa ride around the district. Visit the Capitol Park & Heroes Park to know famous Kapampangan Heroes. Land- marks include the San Fernando Train Station where the Death March ended.</li>
                <li>2. Dine at the famous restaurants in the City. Our distinct cuisine is one of the Ka- pampangans’ Pride. Visit some of the more famous restaurants (Bale Kapampangan, Everybody’s Café, Holliday Land, Fishermans Grill, Jun-Jun’s BBQ and many more) and have a taste of the best Kapampangan cuisine - kamaru(crickets), lichun bulaklak, sisig babi, betuteng tugak(stuffed frog), tocino, buru keng mustasa (fermented rice in mustard), pako salad and many more.</li>
                <li>3. Take home a Parul Sampernandu (San Fernando lantern). It is one of the more fa- mous products of the city and well known not only nationally but also internationally. It has different variations like made of vinyl plastic, handmade paper, capiz, and fiber glass.</li>
                <li>4. Visit the festivals of the City. Drop by and witness the four major cultural attrac- tions of the city - Maleldo (Holy Week), the Pyetang Fernandino during last week of May, the Pyestang Tugak (Frog festival) every October and the famous Giant Lantern Festival every third Saturday of December.
                </li><li>5. Enjoy Shopping. San Fernando is a haven for shoppers. Boasting of having the longest mall in the country (SM City Pampanga) and a premium outlet destination (Robinsons, Starmills and Walter Mart). Soon to open is SM City of San Fernando and S&R Membership Shopping.
                </li>
            </ol>
