            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>The City of San Fernando is strategically located at the heart of Central Luzon. It is 67 kilometers North of Metro Manila.</p>
            <p>From Manila, all bus lines (i.e. Victory Liner, Bataan Transit, Genesis, Saulog, and Five Star) linking Manila with Baguio, Pangasinan, and Ilocos pass through Pampanga. Provincial liners bound for Zambales, Bataan and Baguio City stop over at San Fernando.</p>
            <p>San Fernando City is adjacent to two International Airports – Diosdado Macapagal International Airport (DMIA) which is located at Clark Freeport Zone and the Ninoy Aquino International Airport (NAIA) located at Metro Manila.</p>
